You are helping create a mobile page that strictly follows the project's UI Design System.

## Design System Principles

When the user wants to create a new mobile page:

### 1. THEME COMPLIANCE (CRITICAL)

**Colors - NEVER hardcode:**
```dart
// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
Container(color: Colors.blue)
Text('Hello', style: TextStyle(color: Color(0xFF123456)))

// ✅ CORRECT - Use theme
Container(color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary)
Text('Hello', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium)
```

**Available ColorScheme properties:**
- Primary: `primary`, `onPrimary`
- Secondary: `secondary`, `onSecondary`
- Tertiary: `tertiary`, `onTertiary`
- Error: `error`, `onError`
- Surface: `surface`, `onSurface`, `surfaceContainerHighest`, `surfaceContainerHigh`
- Outline: `outline`, `outlineVariant`

**Typography - ALWAYS use theme:**
```dart
// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded text style
Text('Title', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 24, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold))

// ✅ CORRECT - Use theme text styles
Text('Title', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineMedium)

// ✅ CORRECT - Override specific properties
Text('Title', 
  style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineMedium?.copyWith(
    color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary,
  )
)
```

**Available TextTheme styles:**
- Display: `displayLarge` (57pt), `displayMedium`, `displaySmall`
- Headline: `headlineLarge`, `headlineMedium`, `headlineSmall`
- Title: `titleLarge`, `titleMedium`, `titleSmall`
- Body: `bodyLarge`, `bodyMedium`, `bodySmall`
- Label: `labelLarge`, `labelMedium`, `labelSmall`

**Color opacity - Use new API:**
```dart
// ❌ WRONG - Deprecated
color.withOpacity(0.5)

// ✅ CORRECT - Flutter 3.27+
color.withValues(alpha: 0.5)
```

### 2. RESPONSIVE DESIGN

**Device Breakpoints:**
- Mobile: < 600dp
- Tablet: 600-1200dp
- Desktop: > 1200dp

**Detect device type:**
```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

class DeviceUtils {
  static bool isMobile(BuildContext context) {
    return MediaQuery.of(context).size.width < 600;
  }

  static bool isTablet(BuildContext context) {
    final width = MediaQuery.of(context).size.width;
    return width >= 600 && width < 1200;
  }

  static bool isDesktop(BuildContext context) {
    return MediaQuery.of(context).size.width >= 1200;
  }
}
```

**Use LayoutBuilder for adaptive layouts:**
```dart
LayoutBuilder(
  builder: (context, constraints) {
    final isSmall = constraints.maxWidth < 600;
    return GridView.count(
      crossAxisCount: isSmall ? 2 : 4,
      children: [...],
    );
  },
)
```

### 3. SPACING AND DIMENSIONS

**ALWAYS use centralized constants from `package:common/utils/demensions.dart`:**

```dart
import 'package:common/utils/demensions.dart';

// ❌ WRONG - Magic numbers
Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(16.0))
SizedBox(height: 8.0)

// ✅ CORRECT - Use constants
Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium))
SizedBox(height: Demensions.spacingSmall)
```

**Common spacing constants:**
- `Demensions.spacingSmall` - 8.0
- `Demensions.spacingMedium` - 16.0
- `Demensions.spacingLarge` - 24.0
- `Demensions.paddingSmall` - 8.0
- `Demensions.paddingMedium` - 16.0
- `Demensions.paddingLarge` - 24.0
- `Demensions.borderRadiusSmall` - 8.0
- `Demensions.borderRadiusMedium` - 16.0

### 4. WIDGET COMPOSITION

**Break down into small, reusable widgets:**
```dart
// ✅ GOOD - Composable widgets
class ProductPage extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: _buildAppBar(context),
      body: Column(
        children: [
          _ProductHeader(),
          _ProductDetails(),
          _ProductActions(),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }

  AppBar _buildAppBar(BuildContext context) {
    return AppBar(
      title: Text('Product', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleLarge),
    );
  }
}

// Private widget classes for complex sections
class _ProductHeader extends StatelessWidget {
  const _ProductHeader();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container(
      padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
      child: Text(
        'Header',
        style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineMedium,
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

**Use const constructors:**
```dart
// ✅ GOOD - Performance optimization
const SizedBox(height: 16.0)
const Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(8.0))
```

### 5. COMMON MOBILE PAGE STRUCTURE

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
import 'package:common/utils/demensions.dart';

class ExamplePage extends ConsumerWidget {
  const ExamplePage({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    return Scaffold(
      // AppBar with theme
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text(
          'Page Title',
          style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleLarge,
        ),
        backgroundColor: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.surface,
      ),

      // Body with safe area and scrolling
      body: SafeArea(
        child: SingleChildScrollView(
          padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
          child: Column(
            crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
            children: [
              _buildHeader(context),
              SizedBox(height: Demensions.spacingMedium),
              _buildContent(context),
              SizedBox(height: Demensions.spacingMedium),
              _buildActions(context),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),

      // Optional FAB or bottom bar
      floatingActionButton: FloatingActionButton(
        onPressed: () {},
        child: const Icon(Icons.add),
      ),
    );
  }

  Widget _buildHeader(BuildContext context) {
    return Text(
      'Section Header',
      style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineSmall,
    );
  }

  Widget _buildContent(BuildContext context) {
    return Card(
      elevation: 2,
      child: Padding(
        padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
        child: Text(
          'Content',
          style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
        ),
      ),
    );
  }

  Widget _buildActions(BuildContext context) {
    return ElevatedButton(
      onPressed: () {},
      child: Text(
        'Action',
        style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.labelLarge,
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### 6. SHARED COMPONENTS

**ALWAYS check `package:common` before creating new components:**

```dart
import 'package:common/widgets/button/button.dart';
import 'package:common/widgets/input/simple_fields.dart'; // AppTextField, AppDatePickField
import 'package:common/widgets/toast.dart';
import 'package:common/widgets/linear_indicator.dart';
import 'package:common/widgets/adaptive_root_scaffold/adaptive_root_scraffold.dart';
```

**Examples:**
```dart
// Use shared button
AppButton(
  text: 'Submit',
  onPressed: () {},
)

// Use shared text field
AppTextField(
  label: 'Email',
  hint: 'Enter your email',
)

// Use shared date picker
AppDatePickField(
  label: 'Birth Date',
  onDateSelected: (date) {},
)

// Show toast
showAppToast(context, 'Success message');
```

### 7. FORMS AND INPUTS

**Use flutter_form_builder for complex forms:**
```dart
import 'package:flutter_form_builder/flutter_form_builder.dart';

FormBuilder(
  key: _formKey,
  child: Column(
    children: [
      FormBuilderTextField(
        name: 'email',
        decoration: InputDecoration(
          labelText: 'Email',
          labelStyle: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
        ),
        keyboardType: TextInputType.emailAddress,
        textCapitalization: TextCapitalization.none,
      ),
    ],
  ),
)
```

### 8. LISTS AND SCROLLING

**For dynamic lists, ALWAYS use ListView.builder:**
```dart
// ❌ WRONG - Performance issues
Column(
  children: items.map((item) => ItemWidget(item)).toList(),
)

// ✅ CORRECT - Lazy loading
ListView.builder(
  itemCount: items.length,
  itemBuilder: (context, index) {
    return ItemWidget(items[index]);
  },
)
```

### 9. IMAGES AND ASSETS

```dart
// Local assets (declared in pubspec.yaml)
Image.asset(
  'assets/images/logo.png',
  width: 100,
  height: 100,
)

// Network images with error handling
Image.network(
  'https://example.com/image.jpg',
  loadingBuilder: (context, child, loadingProgress) {
    if (loadingProgress == null) return child;
    return CircularProgressIndicator();
  },
  errorBuilder: (context, error, stackTrace) {
    return Icon(
      Icons.error,
      color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.error,
    );
  },
)
```

### 10. ACCESSIBILITY

```dart
// Add semantic labels
Semantics(
  label: 'Submit button',
  button: true,
  child: IconButton(
    icon: Icon(Icons.send),
    onPressed: () {},
  ),
)

// Ensure sufficient contrast (WCAG)
// Normal text: 4.5:1 minimum
// Large text: 3:1 minimum
```

### 11. PAGE CREATION CHECKLIST

When creating a mobile page, verify:

- [ ] All colors from `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.*`
- [ ] All text styles from `Theme.of(context).textTheme.*`
- [ ] All spacing from `Demensions.*` constants
- [ ] Use `package:common` widgets where available
- [ ] Proper widget composition (small, reusable widgets)
- [ ] `const` constructors where possible
- [ ] `ListView.builder` for dynamic lists
- [ ] SafeArea for proper display
- [ ] SingleChildScrollView for scrollable content
- [ ] Error handling for images/network calls
- [ ] Semantic labels for accessibility
- [ ] No hardcoded dimensions or magic numbers
- [ ] Responsive using LayoutBuilder/MediaQuery if needed
- [ ] Use `Color.withValues(alpha:)` not `withOpacity()`

### 12. COMMON PATTERNS

**Card with proper styling:**
```dart
Card(
  elevation: 2,
  shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(Demensions.borderRadiusMedium),
  ),
  child: Padding(
    padding: EdgeInsets.all(Demensions.paddingMedium),
    child: Column(
      crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
      children: [
        Text(
          'Card Title',
          style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleMedium,
        ),
        SizedBox(height: Demensions.spacingSmall),
        Text(
          'Card content',
          style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
        ),
      ],
    ),
  ),
)
```

**Button styles:**
```dart
// Primary action
ElevatedButton(
  onPressed: () {},
  child: Text('Primary', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.labelLarge),
)

// Secondary action
OutlinedButton(
  onPressed: () {},
  child: Text('Secondary', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.labelLarge),
)

// Tertiary/ghost action
TextButton(
  onPressed: () {},
  child: Text('Tertiary', style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.labelLarge),
)
```

**Loading states:**
```dart
final isLoading = ref.watch(dataProvider).isLoading;

if (isLoading) {
  return Center(
    child: CircularProgressIndicator(
      color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary,
    ),
  );
}
```

## SUMMARY

Every mobile page MUST:
1. Use theme for ALL colors and text styles
2. Use `Demensions` constants for spacing
3. Check `package:common` for existing components
4. Compose from small, reusable widgets
5. Use ListView.builder for lists
6. Handle loading/error states
7. Be accessible (semantic labels, contrast)
8. Follow naming convention: `*_page.dart` or `*.screen.dart`

Review the page against the checklist before considering it complete.
